.SH NAME
Range.getClientRects \- Range: getClientRects() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]Range.getClientRects()\f[B]\f[R] method returns a list of
\f[CR]DOMRect\f[R] objects representing the area of the screen occupied
by the range.
This is created by aggregating the results of calls to
\f[CR]Element.getClientRects()\f[R] for all the elements in the range.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
getClientRects()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
An iterable sequence of \f[CR]DOMRect\f[R] objects.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Logging selected client rect sizes
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]div\f[R]></\f[B]div\f[R]>
<\f[B]pre\f[R] id=\[dq]output\[dq]></\f[B]pre\f[R]>
.EE
.SS CSS
.IP
.EX
